<section xid="1" props="page-margin-right:1.2500in; section-restart-value:1; dom-dir:ltr; section-space-after:0.0000in; page-margin-footer:0.5000in; page-margin-header:0.5000in; page-margin-left:1.2500in; page-margin-top:1.0000in; page-margin-bottom:1.0000in">
<p style="Normal" xid="2" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c style="st0" props="lang:-none-; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-weight:bold">Spike</c><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-weight:bold"> outcomes</c><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica"> </c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="3" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-weight:bold">Name: </c><c props="font-family:Helvetica; text-decoration:none; color:000000; font-size:11pt; text-position:normal; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; lang:en-AU">How does Kivy handle drag-and-drop graphical editing?</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="4" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-weight:bold">Goals:</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="5" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-style:italic">As in the spike plan</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="6" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-weight:bold">Personnel:</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="7" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-style:italic">As in the spike plan</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="8" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="9" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-weight:bold">Technologies, Tools, and Resources used:</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="10" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"></p>
<p level="1" listid="1022" parentid="0" style="Normal" xid="11" props="dom-dir:ltr; list-decimal:NULL; margin-left:0.5000in; widows:0; text-indent:-0.3000in; text-align:justify; orphans:0; list-delim:%L; start-value:0; list-style:Bullet List; line-height:1.0; field-font:Liberation Sans"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-style:normal; list-tag:1023"></c><field type="list_label" xid="26" props="width:0in; font-family:Helvetica; display:inline; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; bgcolor:transparent; lang:en-AU; text-position:normal; text-transform:none; homogeneous:1; color:000000; font-variant:normal; text-decoration:none; font-size:11pt; height:0in; list-style:Bullet List; font-stretch:normal"></field><c props="width:0in; font-family:Helvetica; display:inline; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; bgcolor:transparent; lang:en-AU; text-position:normal; text-transform:none; homogeneous:1; color:000000; font-variant:normal; text-decoration:none; font-size:11pt; height:0in; list-style:Bullet List; font-stretch:normal">	</c><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-style:normal">I attempted to go through the Kivy idocumentation but found nothing that directly related to creating a custom draggable widget. </c></p>
<p level="1" listid="1022" parentid="0" style="Normal" xid="27" props="dom-dir:ltr; list-decimal:NULL; margin-left:0.5000in; widows:0; text-indent:-0.3000in; text-align:justify; orphans:0; list-delim:%L; start-value:0; list-style:Bullet List; line-height:1.0; field-font:Liberation Sans"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-style:normal; list-tag:1024"></c><field type="list_label" xid="28" props="width:0in; font-family:Helvetica; display:inline; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; bgcolor:transparent; lang:en-AU; text-position:normal; text-transform:none; homogeneous:1; color:000000; font-variant:normal; text-decoration:none; font-size:11pt; height:0in; list-style:Bullet List; font-stretch:normal"></field><c props="width:0in; font-family:Helvetica; display:inline; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; bgcolor:transparent; lang:en-AU; text-position:normal; text-transform:none; homogeneous:1; color:000000; font-variant:normal; text-decoration:none; font-size:11pt; height:0in; list-style:Bullet List; font-stretch:normal">	</c><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-style:normal">An example from </c><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">https://bitbucket.org/koszta5/kivydnd/src/facdaebf77c8?at=master showed a button widget which was able to be moved but was deemed unsuitable for our needs</c></p>
<p level="1" listid="1022" parentid="0" style="Normal" xid="29" props="dom-dir:ltr; list-decimal:NULL; margin-left:0.5000in; widows:0; text-indent:-0.3000in; text-align:justify; orphans:0; list-delim:%L; start-value:0; list-style:Bullet List; line-height:1.0; field-font:Liberation Sans"><c props="font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; list-tag:1025"></c><field type="list_label" xid="30" props="width:0in; font-family:Helvetica; display:inline; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; bgcolor:transparent; lang:en-AU; text-position:normal; text-transform:none; homogeneous:1; color:000000; font-variant:normal; text-decoration:none; font-size:11pt; height:0in; list-style:Bullet List; font-stretch:normal"></field><c props="width:0in; font-family:Helvetica; display:inline; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; bgcolor:transparent; lang:en-AU; text-position:normal; text-transform:none; homogeneous:1; color:000000; font-variant:normal; text-decoration:none; font-size:11pt; height:0in; list-style:Bullet List; font-stretch:normal">	U</c><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">ltimately the most useful source from which the </c><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-style:normal">majority of the code comes from was Chapter 3 the book “</c><c props="font-family:Helvetica; text-decoration:none; color:000000; font-size:11pt; text-position:normal; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; lang:en-AU">Kivy: Interactive applications in Python” by Roberto Ullo</c><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-style:normal">.</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="12" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="13" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; font-family:Helvetica; color:000000">Tasks undertaken:</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="14" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="15" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; color:000000">An application was developed which met all the goals defined in the plan.</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="16" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="17" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; font-family:Helvetica; color:000000">What we found out:</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="50" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt; color:000000; text-decoration:none; text-position:normal; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; lang:en-AU">The Builder class is in charge of loading and parsing all the Kivy language. The load_file method allows us to specify a file containing Kivy language rules that we want to include as part of the project. </c><c props="font-family:Helvetica; text-decoration:none; color:000000; font-size:11pt; text-position:normal; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; lang:en-AU">In using the builder class this way we compartmentalize the functionality of each custom widget easily.</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="64" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="33" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-weight:normal">In Kivy there are three on touch events (on_touch_down, on_touch_move, and </c><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt; color:000000; text-decoration:none; text-position:normal; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; lang:en-AU">on_touch_up)</c><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-weight:normal"> which are broadcast to the all widgets on the GUI simultaneously when </c><c props="font-family:Helvetica; text-decoration:none; color:000000; font-size:11pt; text-position:normal; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; lang:en-AU">activated</c><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-weight:normal">.</c><c props="font-family:Helvetica; text-decoration:none; color:000000; font-size:11pt; text-position:normal; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; lang:en-AU"> Through a combination of these three functions and the ListProperty you can track the movements and tell multiple widgets at once how to move across the DrawingSpace widget.</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="34" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; text-decoration:none; color:000000; font-size:11pt; text-position:normal; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; lang:en-AU"></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="35" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">There is an on_translation method is associated with the ListProperty called translation. Once we define a Kivy property, Kivy internally creates an event associated with that property. The property name is generated adding the prefix on_ to the name of the property. This on_translation method allows us to move multiple selected widgets simultaneously.</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="69" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="70" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">Widgets are added as children to the drawingSpace.canvas from the toolbar, the math module is response for scaling the circle to size.</c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="67" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="68" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="65" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="66" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="44" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="45" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="48" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="49" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="42" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="43" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="40" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-weight:normal"></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="32" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-weight:bold">Open issues/risks:</c></p>
<p style="Body Text" xid="21" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; margin-bottom:6pt; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-style:normal">Creating a drag and drop widget with all the implementation necessary took a significantly longer time than expected at well over 12 hours. As this program is made of several files it is easy to lose track of the interleaving parts. Extending this to include more actions might pose considerable risk.</c></p>
<p style="Body Text" xid="23" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; margin-bottom:6pt; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-weight:bold">Recommendations:</c></p>
<p style="Body Text" xid="24" props="text-align:justify; line-height:1.0; margin-bottom:6pt; dom-dir:ltr; orphans:0; widows:0"><c props="lang:en-AU; font-size:11pt; font-family:Helvetica; font-style:normal">Each custom DraggableWidget must now be able to change colour on command and be linked to a pop-up which allows the transitions to be soft coded into the XML file.</c></p>
<p xid="25" props="text-align:justify"></p>
